column21:
@jrmarino , Thank you for the information. I may update the patches in several days (I'm rather busy with my work now).  On the other hand, I may try to push these patches to FreeBSD Ports and it would be good if they were accepted.
For several reasons below, I currently don't use Stunnel:

Newer OpenVPN (may be >= 2.4.x) introduced a new configuration tls-crypt to encrypt its control communication, making it harder be identified and blocked; therefore, Stunnel is not required;
Stunnel with OpenVPN on the server side also requires additional configurations on the client side;
ocserv (OpenConnect Server) seems more easier to configure and more efficient;  So I'm try to make ocserv work well with DragonFly BSD (there is currently a issue with DFly's tun device/interface).

Cheers

